\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\super \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 The answer, from a predicate nominalism perspective of \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93universals\u8221\'94 is obvious - they derive from their utility. If it was not useful for you to describe them both as cats, you would not do this. See discussions about race, othering, etc. }
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Occam\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s razor is expressed in the sentence: \u8220\'93}{\f0\fs24\b0\i1 Entia non sunt multiplicanda pr\loch\af2\hich\af2\dbch\af2\uc1\u230\'E6ter necessitatem}{\f0\fs24\b0 ,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 which means: Only in cases of extremest necessity are we allowed to assume the existence of hypothetical facts. If assumed facts are not absolutely indispensable, cut them off!}{ }
\par\plain 
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Occam\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s razor was invented for a special purpose, that of cutting off the realistic hypostatisation of abstract ideas.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 I do not know which is more startling, that a realist in name, such as Mr. Peirce, should use a weapon forged by nominalists against realism, or that he whom in other respects we found in such a close contact with nominalistic methods, should not understand how to handle a nominalistic weapon.}
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 Mr. Peirce uses Occam\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s razor to cut off statements and facts which make his pet theories dispensable; but he forgets that Occam\u8217\'92s\~}{\f0\fs24\b0 [}{\f0\fs24\b0 578]razor cuts off ideas only, and when it comes in contact with facts its edge is turned.}{ }
\par\plain 
\par\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 possessing a sharp mind, but like many, when coming in contact with the facts, the edge is turned.}
\par\plain {Paul Carus - }{\f0\fs24\b0 His beliefs attempted to steer a middle course between idealistic\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metaphysics"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 metaphysics}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~and\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Materialism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 materialism}}{\f0\fs24\b0 . He differed with metaphysicians because they "}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/reify#Verb"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 reified}}{\f0\fs24\b0 " words and treated them as if they were realities, and he objected to materialism because it ignored or overlooked the importance of form.}{ }
\par\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0 It is claimed that Carus was dismissed by\~}{\field{\*\fldinst HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orientalism"}{\fldrslt\f0\fs24\b0 Orientalists}}{\f0\fs24\b0 \~and philosophers alike because of his failure to comply with the rules of either discipline}{ }
